title: 111_s2071
content: CERTAIN IMAGING COLORANTS are added to the Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States under a new heading in Subchapter II of chapter 99. Certain imaging colorants, including aryl substituted pyrazonyl and substituted naphthalene, are added to the Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States under a new heading in Subchapter II of chapter 99. Certain imaging colorants, including aryl substituted pyridinyl azo alkoxyphenyl azo and copper phthalocyanine substituted with sulphonic acids and alkyl sulphonoamides, are included in the Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States under a new heading in Subchapter II of chapter 99. The Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States includes certain imaging colorants like copper phthalocyanine substituted with sulphonic acids and alkyl sulphonoamides under a new heading in Subchapter II of chapter 99. The Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States now includes copper phthalocyanine substituted with sulphonic acids and alkyl sulphonoamides, sodium salt, and lithium salt under new headings in Subchapter II of chapter 99. The Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States now includes substituted napthtylene sodium salt under a new heading in Subchapter II of chapter 99. The Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States now includes substituted napthtylene sodium salt under a new heading in Subchapter II of chapter 99. This includes various chemical compounds such as aminoalkyl triazinediylbis substituted phenylene azo bis sodium salt, naphthalenylazo substituted naphthalenyl azo carboxyphenylene sodium salt, and chloro substituted naphthalenyl azo. The Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States now includes various chemical compounds such as aminoalkyl triazinediylbis substituted phenylene azo bis sodium salt, naphthalenylazo substituted naphthalenyl azo carboxyphenylene sodium salt, and chloro substituted naphthalenyl azo under a new heading in Subchapter II of chapter 99. The Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States now includes various chemical compounds under a new heading in Subchapter II of chapter 99, including Aryl [Substituted phenylazo] pyridine, sodium/lithium salt (PMN No. P-02-234) in subheading 3215.19.00. The effective date for the amendment applies to articles entered or withdrawn from warehouse for consumption after the 15th day following the enactment of this Act.
